headline: United Rentals (URI): Reassessing Valuation After Recent Share Price Pullback
summary: United Rentals (URI) has been drifting lower over the past 3 months, even as its revenue and net income keep growing at mid single digit and low double digit clips. That disconnect is what makes the stock interesting now. See our latest analysis for United Rentals. The recent 17.09% year to date share price return has softened after a 90 day share price pullback of 17.17%. This suggests momentum is fading as investors reassess how much growth is already priced in. If United Rentals has you...
